 :tx/rationale "AUDIT F-INV-004: Schema Layers 1-4 are hardcoded in Rust, violating C3 (Schema-as-Data). PROBLEM: C3 states 'Schema is defined as datoms in the store, not as a separate DDL.' Layer 0 (19 meta-schema attributes) is correctly hardcoded — it bootstraps schema-defining capability. But Layers 1-4 (~180 attributes covering trilateral, spec elements, discovery, coordination, workflow) are ALSO hardcoded in Schema::default_schema() (schema.rs:200-800). Schema evolution for these layers requires a code change, not a transaction. JUSTIFICATION: This violates C3 at the deepest level. The bootstrap argument justifies ONLY Layer 0 — the meta-schema that defines :db/ident, :db/valueType, etc. Everything above Layer 0 should be transacted as datoms, making them evolvable via the same mechanism as any other data. The current design makes the kernel unusable for non-DDIS domains without forking. This is the most impactful C8 fix because schema determines what the system can think about. SOLUTION: (1) Move Layers 1-4 to .edn manifest files loaded at braid init. (2) Kernel hardcodes only Layer 0 (meta-schema). (3) braid init --manifest ddis.edn installs DDIS schema; braid init --manifest research.edn installs different one. Schema::from_datoms() already exists as the loading mechanism. VERIFICATION: braid init with no manifest produces store with only Layer 0 attributes. braid init --manifest ddis.edn produces full DDIS schema. DEPENDENCIES: This is the foundational C8 fix. Enables F-C8-002 (MaterializedViews configurability), F-C8-003 (trilateral configurability). Also serves as prerequisite for Wave 2 architectural corrections. Interacts with F-C8-001 (which is the same finding from the C8 dimension). FILES: crates/braid-kernel/src/schema.rs:200-800, crates/braid/src/commands/init.rs. SEVERITY: High. WAVE: 2. EFFORT: 16h."
